        <updateDate>2019-09-25T15:59:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p> <strong>Safe Routes Act of 2019</strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation to waive any vehicle weight limit for covered logging vehicles.</p> <p>The term &quot;covered logging vehicle&quot; means a vehicle that (1) is transporting raw or unfinished forest products, including logs, pulpwood, biomass, or wood chips; (2) is traveling a distance of not more than 150 air miles from the point of origin to a storage or processing facility; and (3) meets applicable state legal weight tolerances and vehicle configurations for transporting raw or unfinished forest products within the boundaries of each state in which the vehicle is operating.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
